    2 x <!--855-->Savagery to Match Their Numbers<br />
<br />
  Conditions (4)<br />
    4 x <!--31-->Saruman&#39;s Ambition    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">  The strategy for the Free Peoples side of this deck is relatively simple.  Play possessions and maintain strong companions.  If you win the bid, start Legolas and Arwen so that you can pull out Gimli.  There are enough weapons that the fellowship can cruise through site 4 most of the time.<br />
<br />
  Legolas&#39;s Bow and the flexible pump cards can help keep you alive afterwards.  Only double move if your opponent is near or ahead of you.  Legolas, Gimle, and Arwen can all do more than 1 damage so cleaning up minions isn&#39;t too hard so double moving is possible.<br />
<br />
  The Defend It and Hope&#39;s are in there for Uruk-Hai decks (particularly at site 5) and the Severed His Bonds is for swarm decks.<br />
<br />
<br />
  The strategy for the Shadow side is a swarm of Uruk-Hai at Deep of Helm.  Using the Uruk Regulars and the text of the site, you can get upwards of 7 Uruks there depending on your hand.<br />
<br />
  At other sites you have two possibilities, over wounding companions or providing stopping power, depending on your opponents deck.<br />
<br />
  If you&#39;re playing against a twilight choke or Hunters deck try to kill off all the companions.  Use the Uruk Broods to win skirmishes, Uruk Fighters cause wounds by making them fierce, and Lurtz&#39;s Battle Cry to kill off 3-vitality companions like Gimle or Legolas.<br />
<br />
  Against a large fellowship or Horn of Boromir deck, make sure to stop them from moving so that a few double moves can pull you ahead.  The Uruk Rear Guard is strong enough to stop most companions, and the Broad-Bladed Swords prevent your opponent from killing minions without beating them in a skirmish. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
